89.8	Maria_Callas	Maria Callas	Maria Callas (Greek: ) (December 2, 1923 â€“ September 16, 1977) was an American-born Greek soprano and one of the most renowned opera singers of the 20th century. She combined an impressive bel canto technique, a wide-ranging voice and great dramatic gifts. An extremely versatile singer, her repertoire ranged from classical opera seria to the bel canto operas of Donizetti, Bellini and Rossini; further, to the works of Verdi and Puccini; and, in her early career, to the music dramas of Wagner. Her remarkable musical and dramatic talents led to her being hailed as La Divina. She also achieved success as a cinematic actress, playing the title role in Pasolini's Medea.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/13/MariaCallas.jpg/220px-MariaCallas.jpg
